In this article, President Barack Obama issues a Presidential Memorandum regarding the drawdown of up to $25 million in commodities and services from any agency of the United States Government to support Libyan groups, such as the Transitional National Council. This drawdown is intended to aid efforts in protecting civilians and civilian-populated areas in Libya that are under threat of attack. The Secretary of State is instructed to report this determination to Congress, arrange for its publication in the Federal Register, and coordinate the implementation of this drawdown.